Core Request:
Build a comprehensive project tracking and scheduling application for Georgia Power's reliability projects that manages 700+ projects across 15+ external vendors.
Key Requirements:
1. Project Management:
Track 700+ active reliability projects
Full CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete)
Project details including:
Project name, code, description
Project type, status, priority
Vendor assignment
Start date, planned end date, actual end date
Budget tracking
Location information
Assigned personnel
2. Visual Timeline (Gantt Chart):
Interactive Gantt chart showing all projects
Color-coded status indicators:
Red: Delayed projects
Orange: At-risk projects
Blue: In-progress projects
Green: Completed projects
Progress bars showing completion percentage
Filterable by vendor, status, and date range
3. Vendor Management:
Track 15+ external vendors
Vendor contact information
Performance metrics including:
Total projects
Completion rate
On-time delivery percentage
Performance trends
4. Automated Alerts:
Daily automated checks for:
Delayed projects
Budget overruns
Stale project updates
Projects without recent activity
Alert prioritization
Alert acknowledgment and resolution workflow
5. Smart Action Items:
AI-powered recommendations for next best actions
Prioritized by urgency and impact
Auto-generated based on project conditions
6. Dashboard Analytics:
Real-time overview showing:
Total project count
Delayed projects
Active alerts
Completed projects this month
Projects by status (pie chart)
Projects by priority (bar chart)
Budget overview
7. Technology Stack:
Backend: Flask (Python), SQLAlchemy, PostgreSQL (Databricks Lakebase)
Frontend: React 18, Material-UI with Southern Company branding
Visualization: Recharts, Gantt-Task-React
Deployment: Databricks Asset Bundles (DABs), Databricks Apps
Automation: Databricks Jobs for scheduled alerts
8. Data Import/Export:
Import existing 700+ projects from Excel/CSV
Export capabilities for reporting
Demo mode with synthetic data for testing
9. Databricks Integration:
Deploy to Databricks workspace
Use Databricks SQL for database
Scheduled jobs for alert generation (daily at 8 AM EST)
Service principal authentication
10. User Interface:
Modern, intuitive UI
Southern Company branding (colors, logo)
Responsive design
Multiple views: Dashboard, Projects, Vendors, Alerts
Specific Deliverables Requested:
✅ Flask backend with RESTful API
✅ React frontend with Material-UI
✅ PostgreSQL database schema with migrations
✅ Databricks notebook for alert checking
✅ Databricks Asset Bundle configuration
✅ Demo data generator script
✅ Project import utility
✅ Comprehensive documentation
✅ Deployment instructions for Databricks
Success Criteria:
Manage 700+ projects efficiently
Track 15+ vendor performance
Automated daily alerts
Visual project timeline
Smart action recommendations
Easy data import/export
Deployable to Databricks